1
00:01:31,792 --> 00:01:35,500
Brother, there is a lot of stuff.
Should I sell what's left?

2
00:01:35,917 --> 00:01:38,042
Song, that's inappropriate.

3
00:01:38,207 --> 00:01:40,375
The townsfolk offer them to us for merit.

4
00:01:40,582 --> 00:01:42,500
We shall donate the surplus

5
00:01:42,832 --> 00:01:43,792
for good deeds.

6
00:01:43,957 --> 00:01:44,957
In the next life

7
00:01:45,042 --> 00:01:47,042
-your lips might be thinner.
-What?

8
00:01:47,582 --> 00:01:50,917
I'd rather not be born again
just to listen to your nagging.

9
00:01:52,250 --> 00:01:53,250
Brother!

10
00:01:53,750 --> 00:01:55,082
Please come.

11
00:01:56,542 --> 00:01:59,082
We can't take any more.
Should I row past him?

12
00:01:59,457 --> 00:02:02,667
Nonsense, Song. I want to make merit.

13
00:02:03,457 --> 00:02:04,792
-We can't, Song.
-Yes?

14
00:02:05,250 --> 00:02:07,292
-Preventing merit-making is a sin.
-Is that so?

15
00:02:07,625 --> 00:02:10,125
Okay, we'll stop here.
Help catch the boat.

16
00:02:10,500 --> 00:02:12,250
Wow, Liang.

17
00:02:13,332 --> 00:02:16,875
Are you drunk? You look dewy
like a ripe pineapple

18
00:02:17,167 --> 00:02:20,667
that can't be carried by its stem.
You have to hold the whole thing.

19
00:02:21,542 --> 00:02:23,917
-The current is strong, Brother.
-Are you drunk?

20
00:02:24,207 --> 00:02:25,250
I was asleep last night.

21
00:02:26,207 --> 00:02:27,875
Woke up and got drunk again.

22
00:02:29,792 --> 00:02:31,207
Are you laughing or crying?

23
00:02:35,250 --> 00:02:37,332
Brother is doing well?

24
00:02:37,875 --> 00:02:38,957
I'm fine.

25
00:02:39,542 --> 00:02:40,457
No.

26
00:02:40,875 --> 00:02:42,917
I mean Brother Theng. Is he doing fine?

27
00:02:43,417 --> 00:02:45,917
-Brother Theng went to Tibet.
-Tibet?

28
00:02:46,667 --> 00:02:48,957
So far away!

29
00:02:50,207 --> 00:02:52,207
And didn't even say goodbye.

30
00:02:54,167 --> 00:02:56,582
Can the long-tail boat reach there?

31
00:03:01,667 --> 00:03:02,542
Hey.

32
00:03:02,832 --> 00:03:03,832
Liang.

33
00:03:04,832 --> 00:03:07,250
Are you offering food
to the monk or the fish?

34
00:03:07,750 --> 00:03:10,375
I miss Brother Theng.

35
00:03:17,457 --> 00:03:18,582
That's enough.

36
00:03:18,832 --> 00:03:19,917
I don't need much.

37
00:03:20,375 --> 00:03:21,417
That's right.

38
00:03:21,750 --> 00:03:24,125
-Many people gave alms to you.
-What?

39
00:03:25,125 --> 00:03:27,000
All my life...

40
00:03:27,250 --> 00:03:28,917
Doing good has given me nothing.

41
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:31,417
-What now?
-Even my own wife.

42
00:03:31,917 --> 00:03:34,707
She never appreciated me.

43
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:37,375
Isn't that right, Brother?

44
00:03:43,332 --> 00:03:46,375
That's enough, Liang.
Brother, let's go.

45
00:03:47,167 --> 00:03:48,457
-Wait.
-What?

46
00:03:49,500 --> 00:03:52,667
Girl, bring the fruits to offer the monk.

47
00:03:53,167 --> 00:03:54,457
Yes, daddy.

48
00:03:56,375 --> 00:03:59,750
-Like father, like daughter.
-Namhom coconuts are coming.

49
00:04:00,125 --> 00:04:03,417
-Put them down, girl.
-Daughter taking after father is lucky.

50
00:04:03,500 --> 00:04:06,332
Want some fruits, Brother?

51
00:04:06,875 --> 00:04:08,125
To drink after your meal.

52
00:04:12,667 --> 00:04:14,207
May you be blessed.

53
00:04:15,250 --> 00:04:16,916
-Sadhu.
-Sadhu.

54
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:22,666
Let's go, girl.
Giving coconuts as alms,

55
00:04:23,625 --> 00:04:26,583
we'll be as beautiful in the next life
as we are now.

56
00:04:26,708 --> 00:04:27,833
Yes, daddy.

57
00:04:42,125 --> 00:04:44,500
Song!

58
00:05:06,625 --> 00:05:07,583
Tangkwa.

59
00:05:08,583 --> 00:05:10,125
How good is your English now?

60
00:05:10,333 --> 00:05:13,333
Good enough to go
to England, Teacher.

61
00:05:13,625 --> 00:05:15,500
-Very good.
-Thank you.

62
00:05:15,916 --> 00:05:18,916
Brother Theng went on a pilgrimage.
Will you go as well, Brother?

63
00:05:19,750 --> 00:05:21,583
I can't stay long.

64
00:05:21,833 --> 00:05:23,000
There's temptation by evil.

65
00:05:23,583 --> 00:05:25,166
I'm going to study religion.

66
00:05:25,750 --> 00:05:28,083
Tangkwa, you study the secular world.

67
00:05:28,416 --> 00:05:30,208
-Understand?
-Understood.

68
00:05:31,375 --> 00:05:32,416
Wait a moment.

69
00:05:33,333 --> 00:05:34,583
Anyong haseyo.

70
00:05:35,333 --> 00:05:36,416
Dongbangsin-gi.

71
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:53,000
What's up, man?

72
00:05:53,416 --> 00:05:55,708
I've told you many times,
this is not Wat Samian.

73
00:05:57,208 --> 00:05:58,500
Wait, where are you going?

74
00:05:58,708 --> 00:06:03,000
Joking. We're not going back.

75
00:06:03,458 --> 00:06:05,791
Talk to a monk with respect.

76
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:10,750
-Good morning, Venerable Uncle.
-Venerable Brother!

77
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:12,958
Sorry.

78
00:06:14,291 --> 00:06:15,250
Hey, hey.

79
00:06:15,333 --> 00:06:17,916
You see, today we...

80
00:06:18,125 --> 00:06:19,375
have something to say to you.

81
00:06:19,541 --> 00:06:23,041
Are you leaving the monkhood or not?
Said you'd be ordained for nine days.

82
00:06:23,166 --> 00:06:25,500
But now it's been a year and nine months.

83
00:06:25,625 --> 00:06:29,375
Is Brother getting senile?
A year and nine months or just nine days?

84
00:06:29,500 --> 00:06:31,958
Are you leaving?
Are you leaving?

85
00:06:32,041 --> 00:06:33,375
-Are you leaving?
-Enough.

86
00:06:34,625 --> 00:06:35,750
This is a temple.

87
00:06:36,833 --> 00:06:39,291
-What are you doing here?
-Our songs are finished.

88
00:06:39,500 --> 00:06:41,291
I've prepared your clothes.

89
00:06:41,416 --> 00:06:44,333
-The studio is booked.
-Songs are finished.

90
00:06:44,416 --> 00:06:45,833
I took a shower and waited for you.

91
00:06:46,625 --> 00:06:47,875
Brother Smart is calling too.

92
00:06:48,833 --> 00:06:50,666
-Smart who?
-Smart-ass.

93
00:06:51,208 --> 00:06:54,750
What's up, man?

94
00:06:55,166 --> 00:06:58,125
Song is waiting for me.
Song, please start the car.

95
00:06:58,333 --> 00:07:00,291
I'll give a sermon to my mother.

96
00:07:00,583 --> 00:07:02,500
Yes, Brother.

97
00:07:13,125 --> 00:07:14,916
Bro, what's up with the car?

98
00:07:17,791 --> 00:07:18,958
Full-on.

99
00:07:20,583 --> 00:07:21,916
Acting like a kid.

100
00:07:22,416 --> 00:07:24,666
You've been naughty
since you were a little boy.

101
00:07:25,208 --> 00:07:26,250
Now you're a monk.

102
00:07:26,958 --> 00:07:29,750
I taught you but you never listened.

103
00:07:29,875 --> 00:07:31,750
Visiting your own mother,

104
00:07:32,041 --> 00:07:34,958
why put on such dark makeup?

105
00:07:37,833 --> 00:07:38,708
Mother.

106
00:07:39,416 --> 00:07:40,333
I...

107
00:07:41,041 --> 00:07:43,916
I who have nothing

108
00:07:46,541 --> 00:07:47,458
You see?

109
00:07:50,750 --> 00:07:51,625
Coughing again.

110
00:07:52,250 --> 00:07:59,166
I... I will always love you

111
00:08:00,625 --> 00:08:02,250
You're making fun of me.

112
00:08:02,458 --> 00:08:05,833
I'm not. Don't you know that
back in the day

113
00:08:06,083 --> 00:08:08,583
I sang with those...

114
00:08:08,750 --> 00:08:12,333
old-school singers.
The Elvis of Thailand. Don't you know?

115
00:08:12,708 --> 00:08:16,333
They didn't sing like you do now. Just...

116
00:08:19,375 --> 00:08:20,375
Whatever.

117
00:08:20,833 --> 00:08:24,833
They sang starting in a low voice
up to soprano, a very high note.

118
00:08:25,208 --> 00:08:30,208
With one scream, the glass broke.
Think about that. Like me, for example.

119
00:08:30,916 --> 00:08:31,916
I'll sing for you, okay?

120
00:08:32,500 --> 00:08:39,292
Do re mi fa sol la si do

121
00:08:49,167 --> 00:08:50,125
Mother.

122
00:08:51,542 --> 00:08:55,832
Her voice is like a nightingale.
Why didn't Brother give a sermon?

123
00:09:01,042 --> 00:09:02,750
I told you, mother.

124
00:09:03,042 --> 00:09:05,042
Don't sing such high notes.

125
00:09:05,332 --> 00:09:09,667
I apologize.
The former singer in me took control.

126
00:09:10,875 --> 00:09:12,832
Do you want to hear some more?

127
00:09:16,292 --> 00:09:17,417
It's all right, mother.

128
00:09:18,667 --> 00:09:19,707
That's quite enough.

129
00:09:22,207 --> 00:09:23,542
Oh, you.

130
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:26,625
You're a monk.
You can't touch a woman.

131
00:09:26,792 --> 00:09:27,667
It's forbidden.

132
00:09:29,417 --> 00:09:30,792
It's okay, mother.

133
00:09:31,625 --> 00:09:33,792
A mother is like the saint
of a household.

134
00:09:35,167 --> 00:09:39,750
I'm your son. I can wash or wipe you.
I think it's okay.

135
00:09:40,082 --> 00:09:41,875
Sin or virtue,
it depends on intention.

136
00:09:44,707 --> 00:09:46,832
Moreover, I came here today

137
00:09:47,582 --> 00:09:50,792
because I don't know when will be
the next chance to take care of you.

138
00:09:50,957 --> 00:09:52,042
Where are you going?

139
00:09:53,332 --> 00:09:56,250
I'm going on a pilgrimage to find Dharma.

140
00:10:01,707 --> 00:10:04,792
I rejoice in your merit.

141
00:10:08,375 --> 00:10:10,332
I have something to give

142
00:10:10,625 --> 00:10:14,082
for you to take with you
on your pilgrimage.

143
00:10:15,457 --> 00:10:17,375
-Yes, mother.
-Wait a minute.

144
00:10:38,417 --> 00:10:40,707
-This is a photo of you as a child.
-No matter what

145
00:10:40,875 --> 00:10:43,875
I still love...

146
00:10:44,792 --> 00:10:47,125
you

147
00:11:24,750 --> 00:11:26,375
The woman is me.

148
00:11:27,375 --> 00:11:29,582
And the man is your father.

149
00:11:35,625 --> 00:11:37,625
Goodbye, madam.
I'll give Brother a ride.

150
00:11:38,917 --> 00:11:39,832
Let's go, Brother.

151
00:11:53,167 --> 00:11:57,207
I can't help but feel sad.
You're going too.

152
00:11:58,667 --> 00:12:01,332
Makes me miss Brother Theng even more.

153
00:12:01,832 --> 00:12:05,375
What's the point talking about him?
He went to a nice place.

154
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:09,125
-Brother Theng is dead?
-Not yet!

155
00:12:10,707 --> 00:12:12,207
He went on a pilgrimage in Tibet

156
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:14,792
to find wisdom.

157
00:12:15,542 --> 00:12:16,625
To find wisdom?

158
00:12:17,582 --> 00:12:19,750
What for?

159
00:12:22,707 --> 00:12:26,457
How far are you going to go
for your pilgrimage?

160
00:12:27,457 --> 00:12:31,167
When you run out of gas,
I'll get out of the car.

161
00:12:31,250 --> 00:12:33,417
So you can go home.

162
00:12:33,542 --> 00:12:35,125
How am I supposed to?

163
00:12:35,457 --> 00:12:37,667
Let bygones be bygones.

164
00:12:37,875 --> 00:12:41,167
It doesn't matter when everything happens.
The sun rises

165
00:12:41,250 --> 00:12:44,957
and falls in a cycle.
It's a lesson of life.

166
00:12:45,500 --> 00:12:48,375
-Enjoy yourself, but look at the road.
-Yes.

167
00:13:00,250 --> 00:13:02,125
You, you.

168
00:13:04,917 --> 00:13:05,792
Song.

169
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:07,875
Hey, you!

170
00:13:16,292 --> 00:13:18,042
Did you buy your license,
son of a bitch?

171
00:13:18,125 --> 00:13:20,332
Brother, what are you doing there?

172
00:13:21,082 --> 00:13:23,957
What are you afraid of?
We have a bunch of amulets.

173
00:13:24,917 --> 00:13:25,917
I was just alarmed.

174
00:13:57,207 --> 00:13:59,250
If I didn't hit the brake in time,
we'd be goners.

175
00:14:17,957 --> 00:14:21,042
Brother, end of the road. We can't go on.

176
00:14:21,957 --> 00:14:23,042
Let's go back.

177
00:14:23,292 --> 00:14:25,875
I can't. I've made up my mind.

178
00:14:26,957 --> 00:14:28,582
When we decide to do good,

179
00:14:28,957 --> 00:14:30,582
the road will open up.

180
00:14:31,417 --> 00:14:32,457
So you can stay here.

181
00:14:33,207 --> 00:14:34,125
Then I'll say goodbye.

182
00:14:38,250 --> 00:14:39,582
But Song...

183
00:14:41,582 --> 00:14:42,457
Hey!

184
00:14:44,082 --> 00:14:44,957
Song!

185
00:14:48,707 --> 00:14:49,582
Song!

186
00:14:52,832 --> 00:14:54,457
We're supposed to go back together.

187
00:14:57,875 --> 00:14:58,750
You!

188
00:15:28,417 --> 00:15:30,625
That's not appropriate for a monk.

189
00:15:39,332 --> 00:15:40,457
It's okay to ask for alms,

190
00:15:41,582 --> 00:15:43,125
but not okay to fly like a bird.

191
00:16:14,250 --> 00:16:15,417
That is even worse.

192
00:16:16,250 --> 00:16:17,250
Because I am a monk.

193
00:16:20,417 --> 00:16:21,792
This is how a monk does it.

194
00:17:39,500 --> 00:17:42,041
Good thing it was just an idea.
Didn't really happen.

195
00:18:10,958 --> 00:18:12,916
My alms bowl.

196
00:18:14,458 --> 00:18:15,375
Hey.

197
00:18:15,625 --> 00:18:16,916
My bag.

198
00:18:20,250 --> 00:18:23,541
My umbrella!

199
00:18:25,833 --> 00:18:27,083
I'm a monk.

200
00:18:30,166 --> 00:18:33,458
I've practiced Dharma.

201
00:18:35,958 --> 00:18:36,833
This wind...

202
00:18:40,958 --> 00:18:42,875
cannot stop me.

203
00:18:44,791 --> 00:18:46,083
Earth, water,

204
00:18:47,916 --> 00:18:49,958
wind and fire.

205
00:18:50,875 --> 00:18:51,875
Go...

206
00:18:58,125 --> 00:19:01,000
My alms bowl is gone,
my bag is gone.

207
00:19:01,166 --> 00:19:02,083
My last...

208
00:19:02,916 --> 00:19:04,166
umbrella.

209
00:19:06,916 --> 00:19:09,458
Where the umbrella goes, I go with it.

210
00:19:26,750 --> 00:19:29,500
The highest point is non-self.

211
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:02,916
Ouch.

212
00:20:16,833 --> 00:20:18,416
It burns.

213
00:20:23,250 --> 00:20:24,333
This must be a test

214
00:20:24,958 --> 00:20:26,000
from the Lord Buddha.

215
00:21:47,041 --> 00:21:47,958
You.

216
00:21:48,625 --> 00:21:50,958
You.

217
00:21:51,541 --> 00:21:52,458
Brother.

218
00:21:52,541 --> 00:21:54,541
-I--
-There's a wedding.

219
00:21:54,625 --> 00:21:56,666
The groom's procession
is going to another village.

220
00:21:56,750 --> 00:22:00,375
-No, I mean I--
-A westerner has a wife here.

221
00:22:01,041 --> 00:22:04,916
They're already married.
They brought some friends over to marry.

222
00:22:05,250 --> 00:22:08,833
-I...
-They're Americans.

223
00:22:09,125 --> 00:22:11,375
But we're Thai.

224
00:22:12,375 --> 00:22:14,708
They get married. Many women here

225
00:22:14,916 --> 00:22:17,666
-have married a westerner.
-Okay.

226
00:22:17,833 --> 00:22:19,375
Wow, Brother.

227
00:22:19,833 --> 00:22:21,375
Your robe is all torn.

228
00:22:22,458 --> 00:22:24,458
It's not, it's in one piece.

229
00:22:24,708 --> 00:22:27,708
Brother, you look so beaten up.

230
00:22:28,208 --> 00:22:32,750
From the looks of it,
you're the final stage of monk.

231
00:22:33,541 --> 00:22:36,000
You misunderstood something.
I'm a monk.

232
00:22:36,750 --> 00:22:37,791
Not cancer.

233
00:22:38,291 --> 00:22:39,166
Yes.

234
00:22:39,375 --> 00:22:40,833
Why are you limping?

235
00:22:40,958 --> 00:22:42,458
I got pricked by some thorns.

236
00:22:42,541 --> 00:22:46,250
Usually the thorns here
don't prick anyone.

237
00:22:46,500 --> 00:22:48,333
You must have stepped on it.

238
00:22:48,916 --> 00:22:49,875
I have to go.

239
00:22:50,041 --> 00:22:53,041
I'll see them get married to westerners.
Don't want to miss the beginning.

240
00:22:55,958 --> 00:22:57,375
This must be a test

241
00:22:58,291 --> 00:22:59,583
once again.

242
00:23:10,791 --> 00:23:14,750
I'm going to have a foreign husband,
but I can't speak foreign yet.

243
00:23:16,250 --> 00:23:18,083
What do you want to say?

244
00:23:18,708 --> 00:23:22,250
I'm going to meet the groom, right?
I'm going to say to him,

245
00:23:22,750 --> 00:23:23,791
Honey,

246
00:23:24,375 --> 00:23:27,083
I'm so happy.

247
00:23:27,500 --> 00:23:30,583
-How do I say that?
-It's not hard, Kamlah.

248
00:23:31,166 --> 00:23:33,750
We have a great deal of experience.

249
00:23:34,666 --> 00:23:38,416
Seriously, why do you want
to have a Thai wife?

250
00:23:38,916 --> 00:23:42,666
-Thai women are... beautiful!
-Beautiful!

251
00:23:45,791 --> 00:23:49,000
KOKSA-ARD TEMPLE
KOKSA-ARD KLIANG VILLAGE

252
00:24:09,916 --> 00:24:11,500
KOKSA-ARD TEMPLE

253
00:24:48,750 --> 00:24:50,291
What are you looking for?

254
00:24:53,666 --> 00:24:55,125
If we both take one step back,

255
00:24:55,750 --> 00:24:56,750
would it be embarrassing?

256
00:24:57,750 --> 00:24:58,666
Not at all.

257
00:25:02,375 --> 00:25:03,625
Hello, abbot.

258
00:25:04,750 --> 00:25:07,333
Not abbot. I'm Somkiat.

259
00:25:08,958 --> 00:25:10,625
You can call me Jiew.

260
00:25:12,333 --> 00:25:14,958
-And who are you?
-A monk.

261
00:25:16,750 --> 00:25:18,541
So you've been a monk for a long time.

262
00:25:19,458 --> 00:25:20,458
You look so old.

263
00:25:23,541 --> 00:25:26,958
I'm joking. You're looking for the abbot?

264
00:25:28,625 --> 00:25:31,458
I came to get married today.

265
00:25:32,291 --> 00:25:34,291
I'm very happy.

266
